# ngx_http_heavybag_module - verified-crawler published CIDR allowlist (TEST FIXTURE)
#
# Plain "addr/prefix" per line; '#' comment and blank lines are skipped. In
# production this file is produced offline by a cron job that converts a crawler
# operator's published JSON range (e.g. Google's googlebot.json) into one CIDR
# per line -- the WAF never parses JSON or does DNS. A request classified as
# $waf_type=crawler whose canonical client IP is NOT in any range below is
# treated as a fake bot (403) when waf_fake_bot_block is on.
#
# These are RFC 5737 / RFC 3849 documentation ranges, never real prefixes, so
# the loopback test peer (127.0.0.1) is deliberately OUT of range.

203.0.113.0/24
198.51.100.0/24
2001:db8::/32
